South Africa’s Rand Strengthens by the Most Most This Month Against Dollar

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-09-06T08:19:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/south-africa-s-rand-strengthens-by-the-most-most-this-month-against-dollar.html
The rand appreciated the most this
month against the dollar, erasing an earlier drop.  The currency of  Africa ’s biggest economy strengthened as
much as 1 percent, the biggest intraday gain since Aug. 31, to
7.0584 per dollar and traded 0.7 percent up at 7.0843 by 10:18
a.m. in Johannesburg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  